content.rendered:
One of my favorite restaurants has these mini tex mex egg rolls that I actually have dreams about because they are so good…so I wanted to try and recreate them the other day! For my first time trying, I feel like they actually came out pretty good! They were super quick and easy to make!

The recipe:

In a pan over medium heat, sauté corn, red onion, and bell pepper with chili powder, garlic salt, and pepper for about 5–6 minutes, until fragrant and softened.

Prepare your avocado: dice or mash, depending on your preference.

Place an egg roll wrapper on a clean surface. Scoop 1 tbsp of the veggie mixture into the center and top with a little avocado. Add shredded cheese if desired.

Use your finger or a small brush to apply egg white around the edges of the wrapper. Fold and roll tightly, pressing to seal.

Heat a little oil in a pan over medium heat. Pan fry the egg rolls for about 2 minutes per side, or until crispy and golden brown.

Serve with your favorite chipotle ranch sauce or chipotle Veganaise for dipping. Enjoy!! xx

Mini Tex Mex Egg Rolls

One of my favorite restaurants has these mini tex mex egg rolls that I actually have dreams about because they are so good…so I wanted to try and recreate them the other day! For my first time trying, I feel like they actually came out pretty good! They were super quick and easy to make!
Print Recipe Add to Collection Go to Collections
Total Time 30 minutes mins
Course Appetizer, Main Course, Side Dish, Snack
Servings 4

Ingredients
  

  • 1 can corn drained
  • 1 red onion chopped
  • 1 bell pepper chopped
  • 1 tsp chili powder
  • 1/2 tsp garlic salt
  • Pepper to taste
  • 1 avocado diced or mashed
  • 1 egg white for sealing
  • 15 –20 egg roll wrappers
  • Optional shredded cheese (Mexican blend or Cotija)

For Dipping

  • Chipotle ranch sauce or chipotle Veganaise

Instructions
 

  • In a pan over medium heat, sauté corn, red onion, and bell pepper with chili powder, garlic salt, and pepper for about 5–6 minutes, until fragrant and softened.
  • Prepare your avocado: dice or mash, depending on your preference.
  • Place an egg roll wrapper on a clean surface. Scoop 1 tbsp of the veggie mixture into the center and top with a little avocado. Add shredded cheese if desired.
  • Use your finger or a small brush to apply egg white around the edges of the wrapper. Fold and roll tightly, pressing to seal.
  • Heat a little oil in a pan over medium heat. Pan fry the egg rolls for about 2 minutes per side, or until crispy and golden brown.
  • Serve with your favorite chipotle ranch sauce or chipotle Veganaise for dipping. Enjoy!! xx
Keyword Avocado, Bell pepper, Corn, Red Onion
